Ariana Grande thought that she was getting into the Japanese mode when she supposedly inked a Japanese inscription of “7 Rings” tattoo. The singer tattooed on her hand “七輪” and showed it to her fans on Instagram and this was a proud moment for her until fans pointed out that it when translated to the Japanese Kanji, it means “shichirin,” a small barbecue grill, not “7 Rings” as she originally thought. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-846753 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Ariana-Grande.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1275" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Ariana-Grande.jpg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Ariana-Grande-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Ariana-Grande-200x200.jpg 200w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Although she later deleted the post, that did not stop people from talking about it:   